The Coalition of Esan People in Edo state yesterday said the All Progressive Congress (APC) will win the forth coming gubernatorial elections. According to the Coalition, APC will win the election and that Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu will be the next governor that will hand over to an Esan governor after his eight years. The Coalition also rejected the purported endorsement of the incumbent governor, Mr Godwin Obasaki by Esan professionals, insisting that many people were not consulted. Spokesman of the Coalition, Kenneth Edewele, stated this in a statement that the purported endorsement of Obasaki was rather fueled by personal political ambitions than Esan good. “The All Progressive Congress (APC) will win the forth coming gubernatorial elections. APC will win the election and Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu will be the next governor that will hand over to an Esan governor after his eight years,” the Coalition said. The group alleged that Obaseki’s plan is to hand over to his deputy after his four years in 2024. “His deputy will in turn spend another eight years before thinking of an Esan governor, probably in 2032,” the statement added. While calling on their people to support the APC, the Esan Coalition said those who endorsed Obasaki are made up of a clique of friends and friends of Governor Obaseki surging to take over the political leadership of Edo central by all means. “They are on a mission to adopt PDP as the official party of Esan people and perhaps ambitiously fill the leadership vacuum left behind by late Chief Tony Anenih, Iyasele of Esanland,” the group added.